  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1995 Interview with Olga Kovacs.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] as you were hearing this cannon fire, what happened to the life in the factory and your work and your day and your-- and the conditions there?",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Gradually, there were-- there was less work, and less raw material.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then some time around April 1944, we heard some rumors that the plant will be evacuated further to the west, and they stopped taking us there.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "However, they marched us every day to dig anti-tank trenches.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Under heavy guard, we were marched in the neighborhood, not too far from the camp.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] somehow we were elated, because posters appeared, saying that it's either victory or Siberia.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they said that all the little-- little brooks that they had in town, tiny little-- I mean, little piece of water, they called it brooks, and they had little bridges over it, wooden bridges.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, tiny ones.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They-- they put mines under it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were all connected they say, so that they are not giving themselves up.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But what happened one day, we woke up, the guards were gone, the Commandant was gone with her very collaborating Jewish kapo by the name of Sala, S-A-L-A, who was a nasty collaborator.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] She loved to smack people, even old people, older women, yelling and screaming, and just to-- just to show how-- how good she is with the-- with the SS.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] They all disappeared.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And from one day to the other, the swastika banners were changed to white flags.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Then we figured that this is really the beginning of the end.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
